g.title: G1
g.text: Complete a safe flight in controlled airspace

g.title: C1
g.text: In the context of all the information from the product line.

g.title: S1
g.text: Argue that all the hazards of the flight are sufficiently mitigated

g.title: G3
g.text: The risk of ground collision is sufficiently mitigated

g.title: G2
g.text: The risk of mid-air collision is sufficiently mitigated

g.title: S3
g.text: Argue that the causes of ground collision are mitigated

g.title: S2
g.text: Argue that causes of MAC are mitigated

g.title: G11
g.text: The chances of a loss of battery event are low

g.title: G12
g.text: The chance of loss of control of the UAS is low

g.title: G6
g.text: The UAS (or crewmember) can avoid other aircraft in the operating region.

g.title: G5
g.text: The UAS (or crewmember) is able to detect other aircraft in the operating region.

g.title: G4
g.text: The chance of loss of control of the UAS is low

g.title: S5
g.text: Argue the ability to detect other aircraft is not hindered

g.title: S4
g.text: Argue that the causes of loss of UAS control are mitigated

g.title: G16
g.text: If airspace is congested, a spotter is needed.

g.title: G15
g.text: If airspace is sparsely populated, a spotter is not needed.

g.title: G13
g.text: The pilot and spotters have sufficient training to spot other aircraft

g.title: G9
g.text: Visibility in the OR will be greater than the allowed minimum

g.title: G8
g.text: Precipitation in the OR will be less than the maximum allowed by the airframe

g.title: G10
g.text: Temperatures in the OR will be within the allowed range

g.title: G7
g.text: The wind in the OR will be less than the maximum allowed by the airframe.
